  <h2>What People Report Over Time</h2>

  <p>Individual results vary. But across the clinical trial and thousands of customer reports, a consistent pattern keeps showing up:</p>

  <div class="bl-tl">
    <div class="bl-tl-item">
      <div class="bl-tl-label">Week 1–2</div>
      <div class="bl-tl-text">Throat clearing and morning congestion start to drop off. Some people cough <em>more</em> at first&nbsp;—&nbsp;that’s the clearance phase kicking in, not a bad sign. It means stuff is moving. The clinical trial measured a statistically significant reduction in fatigue by Day 20.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bl-tl-item">
      <div class="bl-tl-label">Week 3–4</div>
      <div class="bl-tl-text">Physical activity gets easier. Stairs stop feeling like a personal insult. The tightness in the chest starts to loosen. Several users report sleeping better because nighttime breathing calms down.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bl-tl-item">
      <div class="bl-tl-label">Week 6–8</div>
      <div class="bl-tl-text">This is where people say it clicks. Breathing feels easier. More stamina. Less of that low-grade frustration that their chest is holding them back. In the clinical trial, 8 in 10 participants reported clearer airways by Day 60. The phrase that comes up most in reviews: “I feel like I got a second chance.”</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bl-tl-item">
      <div class="bl-tl-label">Ongoing</div>
      <div class="bl-tl-text">Continued daily use supports long-term respiratory comfort&nbsp;—&nbsp;especially for people with extended exposure histories. Users report the improvements hold, not fade.</div>
